data.chText: （因痛苦、厌恶等）做鬼脸，做怪相
data.enText: to make an ugly expression with your face to show pain, disgust, etc.

data.chText: 他一尝那苦味，做了个怪相。
data.enText: He grimaced at the bitter taste.

data.chText: 针扎进去痛得她龇牙咧嘴。
data.enText: She grimaced as the needle went in.
an ugly expression made by twisting your face, used to show pain, disgust, etc. or to make sb laugh

data.chText: 做出 / 露出痛苦的表情
data.enText: to make/give a grimace of pain
‘What's that?’ she asked with a grimace.

example: she made a grimace at the prospect

tr: contort the face to indicate a certain mental or emotional state
example: He grimaced when he saw the amount of homework he had to do

value.def: If you grimace, you twist your face in an ugly way because you are annoyed, disgusted, or in pain.

example.ex: She started to sit up, grimaced, and sank back weakly against the pillow...
example.tran: 她坐了起来，露出痛苦的表情，又有气无力地倒在枕头上。

example.ex: She grimaced at Cerezzi, then turned to Brenda.
example.tran: 她朝赛雷斯做了个鬼脸，接着转向布伦达。

example.ex: He took another drink of his coffee. 'Awful,' he said with a grimace.
example.tran: 他又喝了一口咖啡。“真难喝，”他说着做了个鬼脸。

value.tran: （因厌恶、痛苦等）做鬼脸，扮怪相，脸部扭曲
